*Summary*
Error during Import Word Document in Confluence. A particular document contained Russia character has failed to import.

*Steps to replicate*
# Open any Confluence page or create a new page;
# Click 'Import Word Document' ;
# Chose the word document that contained hyperlink with Russian character in it;
# Change *Root page title* with the same title as the Confluence page;
# Select 'Replace' at *Where to import* field;
# Press 'Import';
# We will get the below error message at the next page;

Error Message:
{noformat}
[com.ctc.wstx.exc.WstxLazyException] com.ctc.wstx.exc.WstxParsingException: Unexpected close tag </strong>; expected </em>
{noformat}

*The fact*
Error will only appear when the *Root page title* change to the same title of the Confluence page. If the title is different, the import will works fine.

*Workaround*
You might need to not change the *Root page title* to the same title of the Confluence page.

